# Forsarr War Campaign - Color Usage Guide

This guide demonstrates how to use the custom Tailwind color scheme defined in `js/tailwind.config.js`.

## Color Groups

### Warhammer 40k Theme Colors
- `imperial-red`: Primary accent color (#990000)
- `aquila-gold`: Secondary accent color (#d4af37)
- `mechanicus-gray`: Industrial gray for UI elements (#333333)
- `chaos-black`: Deep background black (#0a0a0a)
- `parchment`: Light paper-like background (#f5ecd5)
- `text-color`: Default text color (#f0f0f0)
- `header-bg`: Semi-transparent header background
- `section-bg`: Semi-transparent section background

### New Standard Color Palette

#### Base Colors
- `base-bg`: Main dark background (equivalent to zinc-900)
- `base-text`: Primary text color over dark backgrounds (equivalent to stone-200)

#### Accents and Highlights
- `accent-bg`: Background color for headers, footers, important elements (equivalent to green-800)
- `accent-text`: Bright text for callouts and highlights (equivalent to lime-400)
- `accent-border`: Border color for emphasis (equivalent to lime-400)

#### Secondary and Neutral Colors
- `secondary-text`: Muted text for subtitles and captions (equivalent to stone-400)
- `card-bg`: Light background for cards and panels (equivalent to stone-200)
- `card-text`: Dark text for use on light backgrounds (equivalent to zinc-900)
- `highlight`: Decorative highlights for headings and key elements (equivalent to amber-600)
- `neutral-text`: Body text on light backgrounds (equivalent to stone-600)
- `secondary-bg`: Alternative dark background for contrast sections (equivalent to zinc-800)
- `footer-text`: Muted text for footer content (equivalent to stone-300)

## Component Usage Examples

### Main Layout
```html
<body class="bg-base-bg text-base-text">
  <main class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <!-- Content goes here -->
  </main>
</body>
```

### Header
```html
<header class="bg-accent-bg text-accent-text py-4">
  <nav class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <!-- Navigation items -->
  </nav>
</header>
```

### Card Component
```html
<div class="bg-card-bg text-card-text rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
  <h3 class="text-highlight text-xl font-bold mb-2">Card Title</h3>
  <p class="text-neutral-text">Card content goes here...</p>
</div>
```

### Callout/Alert Box
```html
<div class="bg-secondary-bg border-l-4 border-accent-border p-4 mb-4">
  <p class="text-accent-text font-medium">Important information!</p>
  <p class="text-base-text mt-2">Details about the alert...</p>
</div>
```

### Button Styles
```html
<!-- Primary button -->
<button class="bg-imperial-red hover:bg-red-700 text-base-text px-4 py-2 rounded">
  Primary Action
</button>

<!-- Secondary button -->
<button class="bg-transparent border border-accent-text text-accent-text hover:bg-accent-text hover:text-card-text px-4 py-2 rounded">
  Secondary Action
</button>
```

### Footer
```html
<footer class="bg-accent-bg py-6">
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4">
    <p class="text-footer-text">&copy; 2023 Forsarr War Campaign</p>
  </div>
</footer>
```

## Legacy to New Color Mapping

If you're updating existing code, use this mapping to convert from legacy colors to the new color scheme:

| Legacy Color | New Color |
|--------------|-----------|
| bg-zinc-900 | bg-base-bg |
| text-stone-200 | text-base-text |
| bg-green-800 | bg-accent-bg |
| text-lime-400 | text-accent-text |
| text-stone-400 | text-secondary-text |
| bg-stone-200 | bg-card-bg |
| text-zinc-900 | text-card-text |
| text-amber-600 | text-highlight |
| text-stone-600 | text-neutral-text |
| border-lime-400 | border-accent-border |
| bg-zinc-800 | bg-secondary-bg |
| text-stone-300 | text-footer-text | 